{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# E-Commerce Customer Segmentation using RFM and Clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "**Project**: Business Analytics - Part 1\n",
    "**Technique**: RFM Analysis + K-Means Clustering\n",
    "**Dataset**: Synthetic E-Commerce Transaction Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup & Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "sns.set_palette("husl")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data Understanding"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('part_1_ecommerce_customer_segmentation.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Shape: {df.shape}")\n",
    "print(f"\nColumns:\n{df.dtypes}")\n",
    "print(f"\nMissing Values:\n{df.isnull().sum()}")\n",
    "print(f"\nDuplicates: {df.duplicated().sum()}")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Dataset Overview**:\n",
    "- **InvoiceNo**: Unique transaction identifier (C-prefix = cancelled)\n",
    "- **StockCode**: Product SKU\n",
    "- **Description**: Product name\n",
    "- **Category**: Product category (Electronics, Apparel, Home, etc.)\n",
    "- **Quantity**: Units purchased\n",
    "- **InvoiceDate**: Transaction timestamp\n",
    "- **UnitPrice**: Price per unit\n",
    "- **CustomerID**: Unique customer identifier\n",
    "- **Country**: Customer location\n",
    "\n",
    "**Business Type**: Multi-category online retailer with international customers.\n",
    "**Analysis Capabilities**: Customer segmentation, sales trends, product performance, geographic analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Data Cleaning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "original_shape = df.shape[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert date\n",
    "df['InvoiceDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df['InvoiceDate'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove missing CustomerID\n",
    "df = df[df['CustomerID'].notna()]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove cancelled invoices\n",
    "df = df[~df['InvoiceNo'].str.startswith('C')]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove invalid quantities and prices\n",
    "df = df[(df['Quantity'] > 0) & (df['UnitPrice'] > 0)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove duplicates\n",
    "df = df.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill missing descriptions\n",
    "desc_map = df.dropna(subset=['Description']).drop_duplicates('StockCode').set_index('StockCode')['Description']\n",
    "df['Description'] = df.apply(lambda r: desc_map.get(r['StockCode'], r['Description']) if pd.isna(r['Description']) else r['Description'], axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create revenue\n",
    "df['Revenue'] = df['Quantity'] * df['UnitPrice']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Cleaned: {original_shape} -> {len(df)} rows ({(original_shape-len(df))/original_shape*100:.1f}% removed)")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Cleaning Steps**:\n",
    "1. Converted InvoiceDate to datetime\n",
    "2. Removed 92 rows with missing CustomerID (cannot segment unknown customers)\n",
    "3. Removed cancelled invoices (C-prefix) and negative quantities\n",
    "4. Removed zero/negative unit prices (data entry errors)\n",
    "5. Removed duplicate records\n",
    "6. Filled missing descriptions using StockCode mapping\n",
    "7. Created Revenue = Quantity × UnitPrice"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Feature Engineering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "reference_date = df['InvoiceDate'].max() + pd.Timedelta(days=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "customer_features = df.groupby('CustomerID').agg({\n",
    "    'Revenue': 'sum',\n",
    "    'InvoiceNo': 'nunique',\n",
    "    'Quantity': 'sum',\n",
    "    'StockCode': 'nunique',\n",
    "    'InvoiceDate': ['min', 'max'],\n",
    "    'Country': lambda x: x.mode()[0]\n",
    "}).reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "customer_features.columns = ['CustomerID', 'TotalRevenue', 'PurchaseFrequency',\n",
    "                              'TotalQuantity', 'UniqueProducts', 'FirstPurchase',\n",
    "                              'LastPurchase', 'Country']\n",
    "\n",
    "customer_features['Recency'] = (reference_date - customer_features['LastPurchase']).dt.days\n",
    "customer_features['AvgOrderValue'] = customer_features['TotalRevenue'] / customer_features['PurchaseFrequency']\n",
    "customer_features['Tenure'] = (customer_features['LastPurchase'] - customer_features['FirstPurchase']).dt.days\n",
    "\n",
    "# RFM Table\n",
    "rfm = customer_features[['CustomerID', 'Recency', 'PurchaseFrequency', 'TotalRevenue']].copy()\n",
    "rfm.columns = ['CustomerID', 'Recency', 'Frequency', 'Monetary']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Features created for {len(customer_features)} customers")\n",
    "rfm.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Customer Features**:\n",
    "- TotalRevenue: Lifetime spend per customer\n",
    "- PurchaseFrequency: Number of unique orders\n",
    "- TotalQuantity: Total units purchased\n",
    "- UniqueProducts: Product variety breadth\n",
    "- AvgOrderValue: Mean spend per transaction\n",
    "- Recency: Days since last purchase\n",
    "- Tenure: Days between first and last purchase\n",
    "\n",
    "**RFM Table**: Recency, Frequency, Monetary for segmentation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Exploratory Data Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Sales by Country\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "df.groupby('Country')['Revenue'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).plot(kind='bar', color='steelblue')\n",
    "plt.title('Total Sales by Country')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Insight**: UK dominates sales (~50%), followed by India, Germany, France. International expansion opportunity exists."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Top Products by Revenue\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "df.groupby('Description')['Revenue'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(15).plot(kind='barh', color='mediumseagreen')\n",
    "plt.title('Top 15 Products by Revenue')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Insight**: Running Shoes, Denim Jacket, and Bluetooth Speaker are top revenue drivers. Electronics and Apparel dominate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Purchase Frequency Distribution\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "customer_features['PurchaseFrequency'].hist(bins=20, color='mediumpurple', edgecolor='white')\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Customer Purchase Frequency')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Number of Purchases')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Customers')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Insight**: Most customers are one-time or occasional buyers. Only a small fraction makes 4+ purchases."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Outlier Analysis\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,3, figsize=(15,5))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(y=df['Quantity'], ax=axes[0], color='lightblue')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Quantity')\n",
    "sns.boxplot(y=df['UnitPrice'], ax=axes[1], color='lightgreen')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Unit Price')\n",
    "sns.boxplot(y=df['Revenue'], ax=axes[2], color='lightcoral')\n",
    "axes[2].set_title('Revenue')\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Outlier Analysis')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Insight**: All metrics are right-skewed with outliers. High-quantity bulk buyers and premium product purchases create valuable outliers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. K-Means Clustering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Prepare features\n",
    "features = rfm[['Recency', 'Frequency', 'Monetary']].copy()\n",
    "features['Frequency_log'] = np.log1p(features['Frequency'])\n",
    "features['Monetary_log'] = np.log1p(features['Monetary'])\n",
    "X = features[['Recency', 'Frequency_log', 'Monetary_log']].values\n",
    "\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Elbow Method\n",
    "inertias, silhouettes = [], []\n",
    "for k in range(2, 11):\n",
    "    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)\n",
    "    km.fit(X_scaled)\n",
    "    inertias.append(km.inertia_)\n",
    "    silhouettes.append(silhouette_score(X_scaled, km.labels_))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(14,5))\n",
    "axes[0].plot(range(2,11), inertias, 'bo-')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Elbow Method')\n",
    "axes[1].plot(range(2,11), silhouettes, 'ro-')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Silhouette Score')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Cluster Selection**: K=4 chosen based on elbow bend and highest silhouette score with business interpretability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Final Model\n",
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42, n_init=10)\n",
    "labels = kmeans.fit_predict(X_scaled)\n",
    "rfm['Cluster'] = labels\n",
    "customer_features['Cluster'] = labels\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Silhouette Score: {silhouette_score(X_scaled, labels):.3f}")\n",
    "print(f"Cluster Distribution: {dict(pd.Series(labels).value_counts().sort_index())}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Cluster Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2,2, figsize=(14,10))\n",
    "colors = ['#FF6B6B', '#4ECDC4', '#45B7D1', '#96CEB4']\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(4):\n",
    "    mask = rfm['Cluster'] == i\n",
    "    axes[0,0].scatter(rfm.loc[mask, 'Recency'], rfm.loc[mask, 'Frequency'], c=colors[i], label=f'Cluster {i}', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "axes[0,0].set_xlabel('Recency')\n",
    "axes[0,0].set_ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "axes[0,0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "cluster_means = customer_features.groupby('Cluster')[['Recency','PurchaseFrequency','TotalRevenue','AvgOrderValue']].mean()\n",
    "cluster_means['Recency'].plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[0,1], color='coral')\n",
    "axes[0,1].set_title('Avg Recency by Cluster')\n",
    "cluster_means['PurchaseFrequency'].plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[1,0], color='steelblue')\n",
    "axes[1,0].set_title('Avg Frequency by Cluster')\n",
    "cluster_means['TotalRevenue'].plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[1,1], color='mediumseagreen')\n",
    "axes[1,1].set_title('Avg Revenue by Cluster')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Cluster Interpretation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for cid in range(4):\n",
    "    data = customer_features[customer_features['Cluster'] == cid]\n",
    "    rev_share = data['TotalRevenue'].sum() / customer_features['TotalRevenue'].sum() * 100\n",
    "    print(f"\nCluster {cid}: {len(data)} customers ({len(data)/len(customer_features)*100:.1f}%)")\n",
    "    print(f"  Avg Recency: {data['Recency'].mean():.1f} days")\n",
    "    print(f"  Avg Frequency: {data['PurchaseFrequency'].mean():.2f}")\n",
    "    print(f"  Avg Revenue: {data['TotalRevenue'].mean():.2f}")\n",
    "    print(f"  Revenue Share: {rev_share:.1f}%")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Cluster Profiles\n",
    "\n",
    "| Cluster | Name | Size | Avg Recency | Avg Frequency | Avg Revenue | Revenue Share |\n",
    "|---------|------|------|-------------|---------------|-------------|---------------|\n",
    "| 0 | Recent Low-Value Buyers | 25.5% | 67 days | 1.7 | ~10,000 | 19.2% |\n",
    "| 1 | At-Risk Moderate Buyers | 24.5% | 232 days | 1.6 | ~11,300 | 20.8% |\n",
    "| 2 | High-Value Loyal | 25.5% | 74 days | 3.4 | ~26,000 | 47.7% |\n",
    "| 3 | Lost/Lapsed | 24.5% | 166 days | 1.0 | ~1,700 | 12.3% |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Business Recommendations\n",
    "\n",
